posts.name: Bekale
posts.cooked:
Hi,

I would like to use this library in my FRC project:

https://code.google.com/archive/p/json-simple/downloads

Can someone tell me how to import this jar file inside my VScode (FRC) project, please? I don’t see a way to add external dependencies.

Any help will be appreciated.

Best Regards

To do it with the jar file : Place the downloaded jar file in a folder called libs or something (using the project directory also works but this keeps it organized) In your build.gradle file in the dependency’s section:

this should work but I would recommend not doing it this way

My recommendation That library you are wanting to use is 10 years old (last update published in 2012) and there are many newer json readers (a great one is gson which is also by Google).

posts.name: Fletch
posts.cooked: Dependencies are managed by gradle, so you could need to add it to your build.gradle file in the dependencies section.  Theres plenty of documentation out there on what the specific syntax needs to be.

posts.name: Andy Gasser
posts.cooked:
I suggest you reference something from a Maven repo, not a JAR file. This way someone who wants to build your project on another computer won’t need to do a separate download, it will happen automatically.

gson is a good choice. We are using Jackson . You can add the lines below to your build.gradle file dependencies section to use Jackson. No need to manually download JARs. Just make sure you’re connected to the internet when building for the first time after you add it.

posts.name: Thad House
posts.cooked: Jackson is actually included by default in WPILib now. No need to explicitly add them. Currently its using 2.12.4

posts.name: Andy Gasser
posts.cooked: Nice! I guess I can remove the dependency. No need to add anything to use JSON, it’s already built in.
